tnSMComMgmtSwRev.name: tnSMComMgmtSwRev
tnSMComMgmtSwRev.description: The downloadable management s/w code revision.

tnSMComIpAddr.name: tnSMComIpAddr
tnSMComIpAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

tnSMComNetMask.name: tnSMComNetMask
tnSMComNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

spsReset.name: spsReset
spsReset.description: Setting this object to reset(2) causes a reset of the hardware. Setting this object to noReset(1) has no effect. The agent will always return the value noReset(1) when this object is read.

spsConfig.name: spsConfig
spsConfig.reference: Port Switching Management Engine HDS. Document Number: xxxx Revision 2.2.
spsConfig.description: The hardware configuration information. The type and size of ROM, RAM, and DRAM.

spsBootpEnable.name: spsBootpEnable
spsBootpEnable.description: If this object is set to enabled(1) the unit will use the Bootstrap Protocol (BOOTP) on power-up or reset to obtain its IP configuration parameters. If this object is set to disabled(2) the unit will not use BOOTP. It will use values stored in non-volatile storage.

spsBootpServer.name: spsBootpServer
spsBootpServer.description: This object specifies the IP address of the BOOTP server the client wishes to respond; forcing the boot to occur from a specific host. If the IP address of the BOOTP server is unknown this object should be set to be the 'broadcast address' 255.255.255.255. The value of this object is not updated by the system when it determines the IP address of the BOOTP server.

spsDefaultGateway.name: spsDefaultGateway
spsDefaultGateway.description: This object specifies the IP address of the default gateway. This object is the same as ipRouteDest for the default route. It is placed here as a single object for convenience.

spsMgmtSegment.name: spsMgmtSegment
spsMgmtSegment.description: Indicates the segment the management interface is on. The value is between 1 and spsMaxSegment. The agent should not allow the NMU to be placed on a segment which has no ports assigned to it, as this would prevent communication with the NMU.

spsIpAddrTable.name: spsIpAddrTable
spsIpAddrTable.description: The table of addressing information relevant to this entity's IP addresses.

spsIpAddrEntry.name: spsIpAddrEntry
spsIpAddrEntry.description: The addressing information relevant to this entity's IP addresses.

spsIpIfIndex.name: spsIpIfIndex
spsIpIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same as identified by the same value of ifIndex (and also ipAdEntIfIndex).

spsIpAddr.name: spsIpAddr
spsIpAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains. The IP address value for this entry is the same value as specified by ipAdEntAddr. This entry differs from ipAdEntAddr, in that it has read-write access, which allows the IP address to be specified using SNMP. The unit must be reset for the new IP address to take effect.

spsIpNetMask.name: spsIpNetMask
spsIpNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0. The subnet mask value for this entry is the same value as specified by ipAdEntNetMask. This entry differs from ipAdEntNetMask in that is has read- write access, which allows the subnet mask to be specified using SNMP. The unit must be reset for the new subnet mask to take effect.

spsTrapTable.name: spsTrapTable
spsTrapTable.description: A list of trap destinations and community names. When generating a trap, each destination in this list is sent the trap using the associated community name.

spsTrapIndex.name: spsTrapIndex
spsTrapIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the SNMP trap destination and community name pairing to which this entry is applicable.

spsTrapDestination.name: spsTrapDestination
spsTrapDestination.reference: A Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP), RFC1157
spsTrapDestination.description: This object specifies the destination address of the Trap-PDU.

spsTrapCommunity.name: spsTrapCommunity
spsTrapCommunity.description: The community name used when generating traps.

spsMaxSegment.name: spsMaxSegment
spsMaxSegment.description: The maximum number of segments supported.

spsPasswdReset.name: spsPasswdReset
spsPasswdReset.description: If this object is set to reset(2) resets the joystick password to a known value. Setting this value to noReset(1) has no effect. The agent will always return the value noReset(1) when this object is read.

spsExternalPowerSupply.name: spsExternalPowerSupply
spsExternalPowerSupply.description: This object indicates the status of the internal power supply. A value of present(1) indicates the power supply is present and able to provide power. A value of notPresent(2) indicates the power supply is unable to provide power or is not present.

spsDisplayString.name: spsDisplayString
spsDisplayString.description: Setting this object changes the contents of the display.

spsRptrGroupTable.name: spsRptrGroupTable
spsRptrGroupTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about the repeater groups (Units).

spsRptrGroupEntry.name: spsRptrGroupEntry
spsRptrGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a single repeater group.

spsRptrGroupIndex.name: spsRptrGroupIndex
spsRptrGroupIndex.description: This object identifies the group containing the port for which this entry contains information. The group identified by a particular value of this index is the same group as identified by the same value of rptrPortGroupIndex.

spsRptrGroupUnitId.name: spsRptrGroupUnitId
spsRptrGroupUnitId.description: A unique string which identifies this unit.

spsRptrGroupInternalPowerSupply.name: spsRptrGroupInternalPowerSupply
spsRptrGroupInternalPowerSupply.description: This object indicates the status of the internal power supply. A value of present(1) indicates the power supply is present and able to provide power. A value of notPresent(2) indicates the power supply is unable to provide power or is not present.

spsRptrPortTable.name: spsRptrPortTable
spsRptrPortTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about the ports.

spsRptrPortEntry.name: spsRptrPortEntry
spsRptrPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a single port.

spsRptrPortGroupIndex.name: spsRptrPortGroupIndex
spsRptrPortGroupIndex.description: This object identifies the group containing the port for which this entry contains information. The group identified by a particular value of this index is the same group as identified by the same value of rptrPortGroupIndex.

spsRptrPortIndex.name: spsRptrPortIndex
spsRptrPortIndex.description: This object identifies the port within the group for which this entry contains information. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by the same value of rptrPortIndex. This value can never be greater than rptrGroupPortCapacity for the associated group.

spsRptrPortSegment.name: spsRptrPortSegment
spsRptrPortSegment.description: The segment number to which this port belongs. This value is never greater than spsMaxSegment.

spsRptrPortSrcAddr.name: spsRptrPortSrcAddr
spsRptrPortSrcAddr.reference: ATT1RX04 (FORESPAR) Four(4) Managed Ethernet Repeaters Data Sheet.
spsRptrPortSrcAddr.description: When spsRptrPortEavesdropping or spsRptrPortIntrusion are enabled this object contains the authorized source address, otherwise this object contains the source address field from the last correctly received frame.

spsRptrPortEavesdropping.name: spsRptrPortEavesdropping
spsRptrPortEavesdropping.reference: ATT1RX04 (FORESPAR) Four(4) Managed Ethernet Repeaters Data Sheet.
spsRptrPortEavesdropping.description: Eavesdropping protection safeguards the network from promiscuous mode stations receiving intelligible data from the network. Setting this object to enabled(1) enables eavesdropping protection. Eavesdropping protection causes the currently transmitted frame to be jammed if the destination address field does not match spsRptrPortSrcAddr . Setting this object to disabled(2) disables eavesdropping protection and the frame is not jammed. All broadcast and multicast packets are repeated to all ports on the same segment.

spsRptrPortIntrusion.name: spsRptrPortIntrusion
spsRptrPortIntrusion.reference: ATT1RX04 (FORESPAR) Four(4) Managed Ethernet Repeaters Data Sheet.
spsRptrPortIntrusion.description: Automatic intrusion protection prevents unauthorized users from gaining access to the network. Conceptually, the source address field of the received packet is compared to the authorized source address. If the addresses differ, the user is classified as an intruder and the data going to the backplane is jammed.

spsRptrPortCollisionLimit.name: spsRptrPortCollisionLimit
spsRptrPortCollisionLimit.reference: ATT1RX04 (FORESPAR) Four(4) Managed Ethernet Repeaters Data Sheet.
spsRptrPortCollisionLimit.description: Selects the consecutive collision count that will cause port partitioning. Valid values are 31, 63, 127, and 255.

spsRptrPortEnableIntruderDetectTrap.name: spsRptrPortEnableIntruderDetectTrap
spsRptrPortEnableIntruderDetectTrap.description: Indicates whether the SNMP agent process is permitted to generate intruderDetection traps.

spsRptrPortDisableIntruder.name: spsRptrPortDisableIntruder
spsRptrPortDisableIntruder.description: Indicates whether the port is disabled when an intruder is detected. Disabling a port in this manner is the same as setting the rptrPortAdminStatus object for this port to disabled(2). The security mechanism will not automatically enable a port.

spsSerialPortTable.name: spsSerialPortTable
spsSerialPortTable.description: The table of RS-232 serial ports. Table only contains information not found in RFC-1316 and RFC-1317 Definitions of Managed Objects for RS-232-like Hardware Devices.

spsSerialPortEntry.name: spsSerialPortEntry
spsSerialPortEntry.description: Table entry for a specific RS-232 serial port.

spsSerialPortIndex.name: spsSerialPortIndex
spsSerialPortIndex.description: A unique value for each port.

spsSerialPortModemControl.name: spsSerialPortModemControl
spsSerialPortModemControl.reference: PC16552D Dual Universal Asynchronous Receiver/Transmitter with FIFOs
spsSerialPortModemControl.description: Setting this object to enabled(1) enables the monitoring and control of modem control lines by the serial port. Setting this object to disabled(2) disables the monitoring and control of modem control lines by the serial port.

spsMonitorSegmentTable.name: spsMonitorSegmentTable
spsMonitorSegmentTable.description: Table of performance and error statistics for the segments.

spsMonitorSegmentEntry.name: spsMonitorSegmentEntry
spsMonitorSegmentEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing total performance and error statistics for a single segment. Regular retrieval of the information in this table provides a means of tracking the performance and health of the networked devices attached to this segment's ports. The counters in this table are redundant in the sense that they are the summations of information already available through other objects. However, these sums provide a considerable optimization of network management traffic over the otherwise necessary retrieval of the individual counters included in each sum.

spsMonitorSegmentIndex.name: spsMonitorSegmentIndex
spsMonitorSegmentIndex.description: This object identifies the group within the repeater for which this entry contains information.

spsMonitorSegmentTotalFrames.name: spsMonitorSegmentTotalFrames
spsMonitorSegmentTotalFrames.description: The total number of frames of valid frame length that have been received on the ports in this group and for which the FCSError and CollisionEvent signals were not asserted. This counter is the summation of the values of the rptrMonitorPortReadableFrames counters for all of the ports in the segment. This statistic provides one of the parameters necessary for obtaining the packet error rate.

spsMonitorSegmentTotalOctets.name: spsMonitorSegmentTotalOctets
spsMonitorSegmentTotalOctets.description: The total number of octets contained in the valid frames that have been received on the ports in this segment. This counter is the summation of the values of the rptrMonitorPortReadableOctets counters for all of the ports in the segment. This statistic provides an indicator of the total data transferred.

spsMonitorSegmentTotalErrors.name: spsMonitorSegmentTotalErrors
spsMonitorSegmentTotalErrors.description: The total number of errors which have occurred on all of the ports in this segment. This counter is the summation of the values of the rptrMonitorPortTotalErrors counters for all of the ports in the segment.

tnTRComMgmtSwRev.name: tnTRComMgmtSwRev
tnTRComMgmtSwRev.description: The downloadable management s/w code revision.

tnTRComIpAddr.name: tnTRComIpAddr
tnTRComIpAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

tnTRComNetMask.name: tnTRComNetMask
tnTRComNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

tnTRComIfaceCapacity.name: tnTRComIfaceCapacity
tnTRComIfaceCapacity.description: The total number of interfaces found in the stack.

tnTRV1Commands.name: tnTRV1Commands
tnTRV1Commands.description: When this object is set to the value of open(2), the station should go into the open state. The progress and success of the open is given by the values of the objects dot5RingState and dot5RingOpenStatus. When this object is set to the value of reset(3), then the station should do a reset. On a reset, all MIB counters should retain their values, if possible. Other side affects are dependent on the hardware chip set. When this object is set to the value of close(4), the station should go into the stopped state by removing itself from the ring. Setting this object to a value of no-op(1) has no effect. When read, this object always has a value of no-op(1).

tnTRV1RingStatus.name: tnTRV1RingStatus
tnTRV1RingStatus.description: The current interface status which can be used to diagnose fluctuating problems that can occur on token rings, after a station has successfully been added to the ring. Before an open is completed, this object has the value for the 'no status' condition. The dot5RingState and dot5RingOpenStatus objects provide for debugging problems when the station can not even enter the ring. The object's value is a sum of values, one for each currently applicable condition. The following values are defined for various conditions: 0 = No Problems detected 32 = Ring Recovery 64 = Single Station 256 = Remove Received 512 = reserved 1024 = Auto-Removal Error 2048 = Lobe Wire Fault 4096 = Transmit Beacon 8192 = Soft Error 16384 = Hard Error 32768 = Signal Loss 131072 = no status, open not completed.

tnTRV1RingState.name: tnTRV1RingState
tnTRV1RingState.description: The current interface state with respect to entering or leaving the ring.

tnTRV1RingOpenStatus.name: tnTRV1RingOpenStatus
tnTRV1RingOpenStatus.description: This object indicates the success, or the reason for failure, of the station's most recent attempt to enter the ring.

tnTRV1UpStream.name: tnTRV1UpStream
tnTRV1UpStream.description: The MAC-address of the up stream neighbor station in the ring.

tnTRV1ActMonParticipate.name: tnTRV1ActMonParticipate
tnTRV1ActMonParticipate.description: If this object has a value of true(1) then this interface will participate in the active monitor selection process. If the value is false(2) then it will not. Setting this object might not have an effect until the next time the interface is opened.

tnTRV1Functional.name: tnTRV1Functional
tnTRV1Functional.description: The bit mask of all Token Ring functional addresses for which this interface will accept frames.

tnTRV1StatsLineErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsLineErrors
tnTRV1StatsLineErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a frame or token is copied or repeated by a station, the E bit is zero in the frame or token and one of the following conditions exists: 1) there is a non-data bit (J or K bit) between the SD and the ED of the frame or token, or 2) there is an FCS error in the frame.

tnTRV1StatsBurstErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsBurstErrors
tnTRV1StatsBurstErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station detects the absence of transitions for five half-bit timers (burst-five error).

tnTRV1StatsACErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsACErrors
tnTRV1StatsACErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station receives an AMP or SMP frame in which A is equal to C is equal to 0, and then receives another SMP frame with A is equal to C is equal to 0 without first receiving an AMP frame. It denotes a station that cannot set the AC bits properly.

tnTRV1StatsAbortTransErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsAbortTransErrors
tnTRV1StatsAbortTransErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station transmits an abort delimiter while transmitting.

tnTRV1StatsInternalErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsInternalErrors
tnTRV1StatsInternalErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station recognizes an internal error.

tnTRV1StatsLostFrameErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsLostFrameErrors
tnTRV1StatsLostFrameErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station is transmitting and its TRR timer expires. This condition denotes a condition where a transmitting station in strip mode does not receive the trailer of the frame before the TRR timer goes off.

tnTRV1StatsReceiveCongestions.name: tnTRV1StatsReceiveCongestions
tnTRV1StatsReceiveCongestions.description: This counter is incremented when a station recognizes a frame addressed to its specific address, but has no available buffer space indicating that the station is congested.

tnTRV1StatsFrameCopiedErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsFrameCopiedErrors
tnTRV1StatsFrameCopiedErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station recognizes a frame addressed to its specific address and detects that the FS field A bits are set to 1 indicating a possible line hit or duplicate address.

tnTRV1StatsTokenErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsTokenErrors
tnTRV1StatsTokenErrors.description: This counter is incremented when a station acting as the active monitor recognizes an error condition that needs a token transmitted.

tnTRV1StatsSoftErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsSoftErrors
tnTRV1StatsSoftErrors.description: The number of Soft Errors the interface has detected. It directly corresponds to the number of Report Error MAC frames that this interface has transmitted. Soft Errors are those which are recoverable by the MAC layer protocols.

tnTRV1StatsHardErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsHardErrors
tnTRV1StatsHardErrors.description: The number of times this interface has detected an immediately recoverable fatal error. It denotes the number of times this interface is either transmitting or receiving beacon MAC frames.

tnTRV1StatsSignalLoss.name: tnTRV1StatsSignalLoss
tnTRV1StatsSignalLoss.description: The number of times this interface has detected the loss of signal condition from the ring.

tnTRV1StatsTransmitBeacons.name: tnTRV1StatsTransmitBeacons
tnTRV1StatsTransmitBeacons.description: The number of times this interface has transmitted a beacon frame.

tnTRV1StatsRecoverys.name: tnTRV1StatsRecoverys
tnTRV1StatsRecoverys.description: The number of Claim Token MAC frames received or transmitted after the interface has received a Ring Purge MAC frame. This counter signifies the number of times the ring has been purged and is being recovered back into a normal operating state.

tnTRV1StatsLobeWires.name: tnTRV1StatsLobeWires
tnTRV1StatsLobeWires.description: The number of times the interface has detected an open or short circuit in the lobe data path. The adapter will be closed and dot5RingState will signify this condition.

tnTRV1StatsRemoves.name: tnTRV1StatsRemoves
tnTRV1StatsRemoves.description: The number of times the interface has received a Remove Ring Station MAC frame request. When this frame is received the interface will enter the close state and dot5RingState will signify this condition.

tnTRV1StatsSingles.name: tnTRV1StatsSingles
tnTRV1StatsSingles.description: The number of times the interface has sensed that it is the only station on the ring. This will happen if the interface is the first one up on a ring, or if there is a hardware problem.

tnTRV1StatsFreqErrors.name: tnTRV1StatsFreqErrors
tnTRV1StatsFreqErrors.description: The number of times the interface has detected that the frequency of the incoming signal differs from the expected frequency by more than that specified by the IEEE 802.5 standard, see chapter 7 in [10].

tnTRV1TimerReturnRepeat.name: tnTRV1TimerReturnRepeat
tnTRV1TimerReturnRepeat.description: The time-out value used to ensure the interface will return to Repeat State, in units of 100 micro-seconds. The value should be greater than the maximum ring latency. Implementers are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnTRV1TimerHolding.name: tnTRV1TimerHolding
tnTRV1TimerHolding.description: Maximum period of time a station is permitted to transmit frames after capturing a token, in units of 100 micro-seconds. Implementers are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnTRV1TimerQueuePDU.name: tnTRV1TimerQueuePDU
tnTRV1TimerQueuePDU.description: The time-out value for enqueuing of an SMP PDU after reception of an AMP or SMP frame in which the A and C bits were equal to 0, in units of 100 micro-seconds. Implementors are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnTRV1TimerValidTransmit.name: tnTRV1TimerValidTransmit
tnTRV1TimerValidTransmit.description: The time-out value used by the active monitor to detect the absence of valid transmissions, in units of 100 micro-seconds. Implementers are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnTRV1TimerNoToken.name: tnTRV1TimerNoToken
tnTRV1TimerNoToken.description: The time-out value used to recover from various-related error situations [9]. If N is the maximum number of stations on the ring, the value of this timer is normally: dot5TimerReturnRepeat + N * dot5TimerHolding. Implementors are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnTRV1TimerActiveMon.name: tnTRV1TimerActiveMon
tnTRV1TimerActiveMon.description: The time-out value used by the active monitor to stimulate the enqueuing of an AMP PDU for transmission, in units of 100 micro-seconds. Implementors are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnTRV1TimerStandbyMon.name: tnTRV1TimerStandbyMon
tnTRV1TimerStandbyMon.description: The time-out value used by the stand-by monitors to ensure that there is an active monitor on the ring and to detect a continuous stream of tokens, in units of 100 micro-seconds. Implementers are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnTRV1TimerErrorReport.name: tnTRV1TimerErrorReport
tnTRV1TimerErrorReport.description: The time-out value which determines how often a station shall send a Report Error MAC frame to report its error counters, in units of 100 micro-seconds. Implementors are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnTRV1TimerBeaconTransmit.name: tnTRV1TimerBeaconTransmit
tnTRV1TimerBeaconTransmit.description: The time-out value which determines how long a station shall remain in the state of transmitting Beacon frames before entering the Bypass state, in units of 100 micro-seconds. Implementers are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnTRV1TimerBeaconReceive.name: tnTRV1TimerBeaconReceive
tnTRV1TimerBeaconReceive.description: The time-out value which determines how long a station shall receive Beacon frames from its downstream neighbor before entering the Bypass state, in units of 100 micro-seconds. Implementers are encouraged to provide read-write access to this object if that is possible/useful in their system, but giving due consideration to the dangers of write-able timers.

tnIntruderDetect.name: tnIntruderDetect
tnIntruderDetect.description: The tnIntruderDetect trap conveys information related to the automatic intrusion detection of the SPS2000. This trap is sent when an intruder is detected.
tnIntruderDetect.reference: ATT1RX04 (FORESPAR) Four(4) Managed Ethernet Repeaters Data Sheet.

sfbrm100SystemTable.name: sfbrm100SystemTable
sfbrm100SystemTable.description: System Information and Configuration table for the xFBRM/xBFFG 802.3ah Managed device.

sfbrm100SystemEntry.name: sfbrm100SystemEntry
sfbrm100SystemEntry.description: Status and configuration entries for a xFBRM/xBFFG device.

sfbrm100SysLocPortIndex.name: sfbrm100SysLocPortIndex
sfbrm100SysLocPortIndex.description: The local port index of the port to which the peer is connected. The local device has an index of 0.

sfbrm100SysSecIndex.name: sfbrm100SysSecIndex
sfbrm100SysSecIndex.description: Secondary index for the table. It is always 1.

sfbrm100SysMRevision.name: sfbrm100SysMRevision
sfbrm100SysMRevision.description: The marketing revision of this device. See http://www.transition.com/pshelp/mrevision.html

sfbrm100SysBootLoaderRevision.name: sfbrm100SysBootLoaderRevision
sfbrm100SysBootLoaderRevision.description: The bootloader revision level for this device.

sfbrm100SysFirmwareRevision.name: sfbrm100SysFirmwareRevision
sfbrm100SysFirmwareRevision.description: The firmware revision level for this device.

sfbrm100SysSerialNumber.name: sfbrm100SysSerialNumber
sfbrm100SysSerialNumber.description: The serial number of this device.

sfbrm100SysBIAddress.name: sfbrm100SysBIAddress
sfbrm100SysBIAddress.description: The serial number (BIA) of the cabinet in which the device is installed. If it is a stand-alone this is zero.

sfbrm100SysSlotIndex.name: sfbrm100SysSlotIndex
sfbrm100SysSlotIndex.description: The Slot number if installed in a chassis. Zero if stand-alone.

sfbrm100SysNumPorts.name: sfbrm100SysNumPorts
sfbrm100SysNumPorts.description: The Number of ports on this device.

sfbrm100SysMACAddress.name: sfbrm100SysMACAddress
sfbrm100SysMACAddress.description: The MAC address used in MGMT frames and IP Packets.

sfbrm100SystemReset.name: sfbrm100SystemReset
sfbrm100SystemReset.description: Set this to reset(1) to cause the system to reboot.

sfbrm100SysIPaddress.name: sfbrm100SysIPaddress
sfbrm100SysIPaddress.description: The IPV4 address of the device.

sfbrm100SysSubnetMask.name: sfbrm100SysSubnetMask
sfbrm100SysSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of the device. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

sfbrm100SysDefGateway.name: sfbrm100SysDefGateway
sfbrm100SysDefGateway.description: The default gateway for the device

sfbrm100SysSNMPTrapMgr.name: sfbrm100SysSNMPTrapMgr
sfbrm100SysSNMPTrapMgr.description: The IPV4 address of the SNMP trap manager.

sfbrm100SysRadiusAuth.name: sfbrm100SysRadiusAuth
sfbrm100SysRadiusAuth.description: RADIUS authentication can be enabled or disabled using this variable. RADIUS Authentication is used for management access only.

sfbrm100SysRadiusServerAddr.name: sfbrm100SysRadiusServerAddr
sfbrm100SysRadiusServerAddr.description: The IPV4 address of the Radius Server.

sfbrm100SysRadiusSecret.name: sfbrm100SysRadiusSecret
sfbrm100SysRadiusSecret.description: The shared secret between the device and RADIUS server. A read returns 'xxx' for security.

sfbrm100SysRadiusRetry.name: sfbrm100SysRadiusRetry
sfbrm100SysRadiusRetry.description: The number of times the device would try to contact the RADIUS server, when there is any communication problem.

sfbrm100SysRadiusTimeout.name: sfbrm100SysRadiusTimeout
sfbrm100SysRadiusTimeout.description: The number of seconds the device would wait for the server response before it times out.

sfbrm100SysDHCPEnable.name: sfbrm100SysDHCPEnable
sfbrm100SysDHCPEnable.description: Enable/Disable DHCP. A reset of the system is needed.

sfbrm100SysTLPT.name: sfbrm100SysTLPT
sfbrm100SysTLPT.description: Enable/disable Transparent Link Pass through. If the Peer's remote link goes down, the link down is passed on to the other end while the OAM channel is still active.

sfbrm100SysTFTPServerAddr.name: sfbrm100SysTFTPServerAddr
sfbrm100SysTFTPServerAddr.description: The IPV4 address of the TFTP Server.

sfbrm100SysTFTPfilename.name: sfbrm100SysTFTPfilename
sfbrm100SysTFTPfilename.description: The Firmware file to be downloaded from the TFTP Server for upgrading.

sfbrm100SysTFTPCmd.name: sfbrm100SysTFTPCmd
sfbrm100SysTFTPCmd.description: To initiate a TFTP upgrading, set the value to perform(1), the systems resets and the bootloader is invoked to perform the upgrade.

sfbrm100SysTFTPServerIgnore.name: sfbrm100SysTFTPServerIgnore
sfbrm100SysTFTPServerIgnore.description: In some configuration, when the device uses DHCP to get its IP address, it also receives the tftpserver address for upgrading. When this variable is enabled the tftpserver address got from DHCP is ignored. This is valid only when DHCP is enabled, else notApplicable(3) is returned. It is disabled by default.

sfbrm100SysMgmtVlanId.name: sfbrm100SysMgmtVlanId
sfbrm100SysMgmtVlanId.description: VLAN Id for the management frames. This is valid only when vlan is enabled. This creates a secure channel for all management traffic.

sfbrm100SysSNMPAccess.name: sfbrm100SysSNMPAccess
sfbrm100SysSNMPAccess.description: The SNMP access to the device.

sfbrm100SysIPAccess.name: sfbrm100SysIPAccess
sfbrm100SysIPAccess.description: IP management access to the device.

sfbrm100SysLastGaspPdu.name: sfbrm100SysLastGaspPdu
sfbrm100SysLastGaspPdu.description: This mib variable is used to choose the type of PDU to be generated on the last gasp event.

sfbrm100SysLastGaspPort.name: sfbrm100SysLastGaspPort
sfbrm100SysLastGaspPort.description: When there are multiple OAM enabled ports, this variable decides which port to send the Dying gasp OAM PDU. The default is Port 2. This variable is valid only when sfbrm100SysLastGaspPdu is set to oamDyingGaspPdu(2).

sfbrm100SysLocalLPT.name: sfbrm100SysLocalLPT
sfbrm100SysLocalLPT.description: When the monitored port (sfbrm100SysLPTPort)link goes down, the other port is brought down when this is enabled. This is also named as Selective Link Pass Through.

sfbrm100SysLPTPort.name: sfbrm100SysLPTPort
sfbrm100SysLPTPort.description: This determines the port, on which the Transparent Link pass through and the Selective/local Link pass through will be active. Any link change on this port activates the TLPT and LocalLPT. This is should be the port with active OAM session.

sfbrm100SysAutoUpgrade.name: sfbrm100SysAutoUpgrade
sfbrm100SysAutoUpgrade.description: When enabled, auto upgrade of this device can be done by its peer. By default this is 'enabled(1)'. When disabled, the peer should do a Force upgrade in order to override this variable. Auto upgrade feature affects when this device is in 'passive' mode during the OAM session and is running a different firmware than its peer.

sfbrm100SysFormFactorSlot.name: sfbrm100SysFormFactorSlot
sfbrm100SysFormFactorSlot.description: This read-only variable gives the number of slots in a chassis this unit occupies if its a chassis card.

sfbrm100SysFormFactorPort.name: sfbrm100SysFormFactorPort
sfbrm100SysFormFactorPort.description: This read-only variables gives type of ports present on this board. The values and description for each board : 1 - xFBRM 10/100BaseT to 100BaseFx 2 - xFBRM 100BaseFx to 1000BaseX 3 - xBFFG 1000BaseX to 1000BaseX 4 - xBFFG 10/100/1000BaseT to 1000BaseX 5 - xFBRM 10/100BaseT to 2x100BaseFx 6 - xBFFG 10/100/1000BaseT to 2x1000BaseX

sfbrm100SysOAMPort.name: sfbrm100SysOAMPort
sfbrm100SysOAMPort.description: When only one OAM session is allowed, this determines the port that will be used for sending and receiving OAM messages. This also restricts the number of manageable remotes to be 1. All other ports have OAM admin state will be disabled, this will affect the current OAM sessions.

sfbrm100SwEntry.name: sfbrm100SwEntry
sfbrm100SwEntry.description: Status and configuration entries for switch setting.

sfbrm100SwPortIndex.name: sfbrm100SwPortIndex
sfbrm100SwPortIndex.description: The Local Port Index of the local port to which the peer is connected. The local device has the port index of 0.

sfbrm100SwSecIndex.name: sfbrm100SwSecIndex
sfbrm100SwSecIndex.description: Secondary index for the table. It is always 1.

sfbrm100SwATUAgeTimeout.name: sfbrm100SwATUAgeTimeout
sfbrm100SwATUAgeTimeout.description: The ATU ageing time in seconds. This indicates the time that each ATU entry remains valid in the database before being purged. The minimum aging time is 15 seconds and maximum is 64 minutes. A ageing time time of zero disables ageing. i.e All addresses remain in the database, they are never purged. The aging time should be in 15 sec increments.

sfbrm100SwIngressMonPort.name: sfbrm100SwIngressMonPort
sfbrm100SwIngressMonPort.description: The Ingress monitor port. Frames that are targeted towards an Ingress monitor port go out this port. Not-applicable for a 2-Port device.

sfbrm100SwEgressMonPort.name: sfbrm100SwEgressMonPort
sfbrm100SwEgressMonPort.description: The egress monitor port. Frames that are targeted towards an Egress monitor port go out this port. Not-applicable for a 2-Port device.

sfbrm100SwFactoryDefaults.name: sfbrm100SwFactoryDefaults
sfbrm100SwFactoryDefaults.description: Reset the switch to factory default settings. A read always returns a notApplicable(2) value.

sfbrm100SwResetCounters.name: sfbrm100SwResetCounters
sfbrm100SwResetCounters.description: Resets all port counters. A read always returns a notApplicable(2) value.

sfbrm100SwHistMode.name: sfbrm100SwHistMode
sfbrm100SwHistMode.description: The port histogram counters can be set to : cntRx (1) - count Rx frames only. cntTx (2) - count Tx frames only cntRxTx (3) - count Rx and Tx frames. This affects the histogram counters.

sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap0.name: sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap0
sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap0.description: All Frames with priority 0 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap1.name: sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap1
sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap1.description: All Frames with priority 1 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap2.name: sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap2
sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap2.description: All Frames with priority 2 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap3.name: sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap3
sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap3.description: All Frames with priority 3 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap4.name: sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap4
sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap4.description: All Frames with priority 4 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap5.name: sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap5
sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap5.description: All Frames with priority 5 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap6.name: sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap6
sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap6.description: All Frames with priority 6 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap7.name: sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap7
sfbrm100SwIEEEPriRemap7.description: All Frames with priority 7 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100SwFlushFdb.name: sfbrm100SwFlushFdb
sfbrm100SwFlushFdb.description: Flushes all static entries in the forwarding database. When set to flushAll(1), all the entries in the database are purged. when set to flushNonStatic(2), all non-static entries in the database are flushed. A read always returns doNothing(3).

sfbrm100SwFlushVlandb.name: sfbrm100SwFlushVlandb
sfbrm100SwFlushVlandb.description: Flushes all VLAN entries in the database. When set to flushAll(1), all VLAN entries in the database are purged, and VLAN is disabled automatically. A read always returns doNothing(2).

sfbrm100SwUseDoubleTagData.name: sfbrm100SwUseDoubleTagData
sfbrm100SwUseDoubleTagData.description: When Double tagging is enabled on any of the ports, this mib variable decides if the tag that is removed from Ingress frames should be used or ignored when making switching decision on the frame.

sfbrm100SwFiberRedundancy.name: sfbrm100SwFiberRedundancy
sfbrm100SwFiberRedundancy.description: This feature is applicable in the xFBRM/xBFFG series which have 2 fiber ports. When set to enabled, the primary and backup fiber ports are assumed to be connected to the same destination. Only one of these paths will be active at any given time, and the configuration settings kept in sync between the ports. When set to disabled, the primary and backup ports are assumed to be connected to different destinations, and lose their special functions.

sfbrm100SwFiberRedundRevert.name: sfbrm100SwFiberRedundRevert
sfbrm100SwFiberRedundRevert.description: This mib variable is applicable only if 'sfbrm100SwFiberRedundancy' is enabled. When there is a failure in the primary and secondary fiber takes over, this determines what happens when primary comes back again. Does the link switch back to primary or the secondary takes over as the primary link.

sfbrm100SwFbrRedundActivePort.name: sfbrm100SwFbrRedundActivePort
sfbrm100SwFbrRedundActivePort.description: This mib variable is applicable only if 'sfbrm100SwFiberRedundancy' is enabled. This indicates the current active port that is operational as the primary link.

sfbrm100SwSupressVlanViolations.name: sfbrm100SwSupressVlanViolations
sfbrm100SwSupressVlanViolations.description: This supresses all VLAN database violations and the traps caused by these events.

sfbrm100SwSupressMACViolations.name: sfbrm100SwSupressMACViolations
sfbrm100SwSupressMACViolations.description: This supresses all MAC database violations and the traps caused by these events.

sfbrm100SwIPPrioEntry.name: sfbrm100SwIPPrioEntry
sfbrm100SwIPPrioEntry.description: Each entry represents the remapped value for each traffic class.

sfbrm100SwIPPrioPortIndex.name: sfbrm100SwIPPrioPortIndex
sfbrm100SwIPPrioPortIndex.description: The Local port to which the device is connected. The local device has the port index as zero.

sfbrm100SwIPPrioIndex.name: sfbrm100SwIPPrioIndex
sfbrm100SwIPPrioIndex.description: The IP traffic class remap table index.

sfbrm100SwIPPrioRemap.name: sfbrm100SwIPPrioRemap
sfbrm100SwIPPrioRemap.description: The IP traffic class defined by sfbrm100SwIPPrioTC, is given the priority value set in this variable.

sfbrm100PortEntry.name: sfbrm100PortEntry
sfbrm100PortEntry.description: Status and configuration entries for a each port on the device.

sfbrm100PortLocIndex.name: sfbrm100PortLocIndex
sfbrm100PortLocIndex.description: Uniquely indentifies each port on the device.

sfbrm100PortRmtIndex.name: sfbrm100PortRmtIndex
sfbrm100PortRmtIndex.description: Uniquely indentifies each port on the peer device.

sfbrm100PortConnType.name: sfbrm100PortConnType
sfbrm100PortConnType.description: The actual physical connector on the port.

sfbrm100PortOAMState.name: sfbrm100PortOAMState
sfbrm100PortOAMState.description: This object is used to provision the default administrative enable/disable of OAM on this interface.

sfbrm100PortOAMModeCtrl.name: sfbrm100PortOAMModeCtrl
sfbrm100PortOAMModeCtrl.description: This object can be used to provision the OAM mode for this interface. In auto(1) mode , the interface is set to active/passive depending on if the board is in a chassis or stand-alone. The manual(2) mode lets the user choose the OAM mode (active/passive).

sfbrm100PortRmtLoopback.name: sfbrm100PortRmtLoopback
sfbrm100PortRmtLoopback.description: Initiates remote loopback, if supported by remote peer.

sfbrm100PortIgnoreLoopback.name: sfbrm100PortIgnoreLoopback
sfbrm100PortIgnoreLoopback.description: If enabled, the device ignores any loopback requests.

sfbrm100PortAdvPause.name: sfbrm100PortAdvPause
sfbrm100PortAdvPause.description: Specifies the Pause frame advertisement capability.

sfbrm100PortAdv1000FDX.name: sfbrm100PortAdv1000FDX
sfbrm100PortAdv1000FDX.description: This configuration setting controls whether or not this port advertises willingness to connect at 1000Mbps, full duplex. This is ignored when autonegotiation is disabled, read-only value notApplicable(3)is returned. This is valid only for Gigabit Ports and not valid for fiber ports.

sfbrm100PortAdv1000HDX.name: sfbrm100PortAdv1000HDX
sfbrm100PortAdv1000HDX.description: This configuration setting controls whether or not this port advertises willingness to connect at 1000Mbps, half duplex. This is ignored when autonegotiation is disabled, read-only value notApplicable(3)is returned. This is valid only for Gigabit Ports and not valid for fiber ports.

sfbrm100PortAdv100FDX.name: sfbrm100PortAdv100FDX
sfbrm100PortAdv100FDX.description: This configuration setting controls whether or not this port advertises willingness to connect at 100Mbps, full duplex. This is ignored when autonegotiation is disabled, read-only value notApplicable(3)is returned. This is not valid on Fiber ports.

sfbrm100PortAdv100HDX.name: sfbrm100PortAdv100HDX
sfbrm100PortAdv100HDX.description: This configuration setting controls whether or not this port advertises willingness to connect at 100Mbps, half duplex. This is ignored when autonegotiation is disabled, read-only value notApplicable(3)is returned. This is not valid on Fiber ports.

sfbrm100PortAdv10FDX.name: sfbrm100PortAdv10FDX
sfbrm100PortAdv10FDX.description: This configuration setting controls whether or not this port advertises willingness to connect at 10Mbps, full duplex. This is ignored when autonegotiation is disabled, read-only value notApplicable(3)is returned. This is not valid on Fiber ports.

sfbrm100PortAdv10HDX.name: sfbrm100PortAdv10HDX
sfbrm100PortAdv10HDX.description: This configuration setting controls whether or not this port advertises willingness to connect at 100Mbps, half duplex. This is ignored when autonegotiation is disabled, read-only value notApplicable(3)is returned. This is not valid on Fiber ports.

sfbrm100PortFDuplex.name: sfbrm100PortFDuplex
sfbrm100PortFDuplex.description: This is a configuration setting that controls the duplex mode; fullDuplex is full duplex and halfDuplex is half duplex. This is valid only when autonegotiation is disabled.

sfbrm100PortFSpeed.name: sfbrm100PortFSpeed
sfbrm100PortFSpeed.description: This is a configuration setting that controls the speed; This is valid only when autonegotiation is disabled.

sfbrm100PortLpAutonegAbility.name: sfbrm100PortLpAutonegAbility
sfbrm100PortLpAutonegAbility.description: The autonegotiation advertisement mode can be set using the options of this variable. spdAutoDupAuto(1) - Advertise all speed and duplex supported. spd1000DupAuto(2) - Advertise 1000Mbps with duplex as full and half spd100DupAuto(3) - Advertise 100Mbps with duplex as full and half spd10DupAuto(4) - Advertise 10Mbps with duplex as full and half spdAutoDupFull(5) - Advertise all speeds (10, 100, 1000 Mbps) with Full duplex spdAutoDupHalf(6) - Advertise all speeds (10, 100, 1000 Mbps) with Half duplex spd1000DupFull(7) - Advertise 1000Mbps full duplex spd1000DupHalf(8) - Advertise 1000Mbps half duplex spd100DupFull(9) - Advertise 100Mbps full duplex spd100DupHalf(10) - Advertise 100Mbps half duplex spd10DupFull(11) - Advertise 10Mbps full duplex spd10DupHalf(12) - Advertise 10Mbps half duplex Read-only value notApplicable returned when autonegotiation is disabled.

sfbrm100PortAutonegState.name: sfbrm100PortAutonegState
sfbrm100PortAutonegState.description: The autonegotiation state or if autonegotiation is disabled it returns resolved(1).

sfbrm100PortDuplex.name: sfbrm100PortDuplex
sfbrm100PortDuplex.description: The port's duplex value when autonegotiation is resolved.

sfbrm100PortSpeed.name: sfbrm100PortSpeed
sfbrm100PortSpeed.description: The port's duplex value when autonegotiation is resolved

sfbrm100PortFEFI.name: sfbrm100PortFEFI
sfbrm100PortFEFI.description: Enabled/Disable Far-end Fault detection. Read-only value notApplicable is returned for unsupported Ethernet PHY's.

sfbrm100PortAutocross.name: sfbrm100PortAutocross
sfbrm100PortAutocross.description: This is applicable for supporting PHY's. If set to mdi(1) the transmit happens on pair 1 & 2 and receive on 3 & 4. If set to mdiX(2) the transmit happens on 3 & 4 and receive on 1 & 2. If set to autoCross(3) - automatic crossover is enabled.

sfbrm100PortLock.name: sfbrm100PortLock
sfbrm100PortLock.description: When enabled, it disables the automatic learning of source addresses on this port and drops frames where the SA does not exist in the ATU, and originates a ATU Miss Violation Trap.

sfbrm100PortIgnoreWrongData.name: sfbrm100PortIgnoreWrongData
sfbrm100PortIgnoreWrongData.description: Ignores interrupts caused by reception of frames whose source address is not assigned to this port. When disabled(2), generates a SNMP trap every time a frame is received with SA not belonging to this Port.

sfbrm100PortIGMPSnoop.name: sfbrm100PortIGMPSnoop
sfbrm100PortIGMPSnoop.description: When enabled all IGMP frames are directed to the CPU overriding the Destination address.

sfbrm100PortDoubleTagging.name: sfbrm100PortDoubleTagging
sfbrm100PortDoubleTagging.description: When set to enabled, the frames which have 802.3ac tag with IEEE standard ether-type of 0x8100 are examined for tags. On Ingress frames : All untagged frames remain untagged, all single tagged will become untagged and all double tagged frames will be single tagged on ingress. On Egress frames : All frames exit with a extra tag. All untagged frames get a single tag. All single tagged frames gets double tagged.

sfbrm100PortUseIPTC.name: sfbrm100PortUseIPTC
sfbrm100PortUseIPTC.description: When enabled, IP priority fields are used for Traffic class of priority data.

sfbrm100PortUseTagTC.name: sfbrm100PortUseTagTC
sfbrm100PortUseTagTC.description: When enabled, the IEEE 802.1p fields are used for traffic class of priority data if the frame is IEEE 802.1ac tagged.

sfbrm100PortUseBothTC.name: sfbrm100PortUseBothTC
sfbrm100PortUseBothTC.description: When a frame has both IP priority fields and IEEE 802.1ac tags and both sfbrm100PortUseIPTC and sfbrm100PortUseTagTC are enabled then this mib variable is used to decide which traffic class to use.

sfbrm100PortVLANTunnel.name: sfbrm100PortVLANTunnel
sfbrm100PortVLANTunnel.description: For all unicast and multicast frames with destination address defined as 'static' in the address database port-based VLAN masking, 802.1Q VLAN membership masking and trunk masking are enforced. When this mib variable is enabled, these rules are bypassed for all frames ingressing this port, whose destination address is 'static' in the database.

sfbrm100PortFwdUnknown.name: sfbrm100PortFwdUnknown
sfbrm100PortFwdUnknown.description: When enabled, all unicast frames with unknown destination address are allowed to egress this port( assuming VLAN settings allow this frame to egress).

sfbrm100PortDefForward.name: sfbrm100PortDefForward
sfbrm100PortDefForward.description: When enabled, all multicast frames with unknown destination address are allowed to egress this port( assuming VLAN settings allow this frame to egress).

sfbrm100PortAdminState.name: sfbrm100PortAdminState
sfbrm100PortAdminState.description: Set port state administratively up or down.

sfbrm100PortVTUPriOverride.name: sfbrm100PortVTUPriOverride
sfbrm100PortVTUPriOverride.description: When disabled, normal switch operation is done. When enabled, VTU Priority override occurs. i.e The determined VID priority takes precedence over all other priorities of that frame as per the VLAN database.

sfbrm100PortSAPriOverride.name: sfbrm100PortSAPriOverride
sfbrm100PortSAPriOverride.description: When enabled, Source address decides the priority as per the address database entry rules.

sfbrm100PortDAPriOverride.name: sfbrm100PortDAPriOverride
sfbrm100PortDAPriOverride.description: When enabled, Destination address decides the priority as per the address database entry rules.

sfbrm100PortVLANStatus.name: sfbrm100PortVLANStatus
sfbrm100PortVLANStatus.description: 802.1Q VLAN setting : vlanDisabled - 802.1Q is disabled. fallback - The frame is not discarded if the VID is not in the VLAN Db. check - The VID must be in the VLAN Db, the ingress port may or may not be a member. If the VID is not in the VLAN Db, it is discarded. secure - The VID must be in the VLAN Db and the ingresss port should be a member of the VLAN, else it is discarded. In all the three cases when 802.1Q is enabled, the frame is allowed to egress only if the egress port is a member of the VLAN. In 'fallback' mode, if VID is not in the VLAN db, the frame is allowed to egress based on Port Based VLAN.

sfbrm100PortDiscardTagged.name: sfbrm100PortDiscardTagged
sfbrm100PortDiscardTagged.description: All ingress tagged frames are discarded if enabled.

sfbrm100PortDiscardUntagged.name: sfbrm100PortDiscardUntagged
sfbrm100PortDiscardUntagged.description: All untagged ingress frames are discarded if enabled.

sfbrm100PortEgressMonitor.name: sfbrm100PortEgressMonitor
sfbrm100PortEgressMonitor.description: Any frame that egress this port is also sent to the egress monitor destination port. Not applicable for 2-port device.

sfbrm100PortIngressMonitor.name: sfbrm100PortIngressMonitor
sfbrm100PortIngressMonitor.description: Any frame that ingress this port is also sent to the ingress monitor destination port. Not applicable for 2-port device

sfbrm100PortPri3IngressRateCtrl.name: sfbrm100PortPri3IngressRateCtrl
sfbrm100PortPri3IngressRateCtrl.description: Ingress rate limit for Priority 3 frames, but not faster than port speed.

sfbrm100PortPri2IngressRateCtrl.name: sfbrm100PortPri2IngressRateCtrl
sfbrm100PortPri2IngressRateCtrl.description: Ingress rate limit for Priority 2 frames, but not faster than port speed.

sfbrm100PortPri1IngressRateCtrl.name: sfbrm100PortPri1IngressRateCtrl
sfbrm100PortPri1IngressRateCtrl.description: Ingress rate limit for Priority 1 frames, but not faster than port speed.

sfbrm100PortPri0IngressRate.name: sfbrm100PortPri0IngressRate
sfbrm100PortPri0IngressRate.description: Ingress rate for Priority 0 frames in bits per second, but not faster than port speed. Priority 0 frames are discarded after the ingress rate selected is reached or exceeded. The rates of 128M and 256M are valid for Gigabit ports only.

sfbrm100PortIngressLimitMode.name: sfbrm100PortIngressLimitMode
sfbrm100PortIngressLimitMode.description: Ingress Limit mode. all(1) - Limits and counts all frames bCastMCastFloodedUCast(2) - Limits and counts all broadcast, multicast and flooded unicast frames. bCastMCastOnly(3) - Limits and counts all broadcast and multicast frames only. bCastOnly(4) - Limits and counts only broadcast frames. If a frame is not limited by the above setting, its size is not counted against the limit of the other frames.

sfbrm100PortEgressRate.name: sfbrm100PortEgressRate
sfbrm100PortEgressRate.description: Egress priority rate in bits per seconds. This affects the port's effective transmission rate.

sfbrm100PortDefaultPriority.name: sfbrm100PortDefaultPriority
sfbrm100PortDefaultPriority.description: The default priority of the frame if its not IEEE tagged or not IP frames or no other priority overides are active for this frame.

sfbrm100PortForceDefVLANId.name: sfbrm100PortForceDefVLANId
sfbrm100PortForceDefVLANId.description: Force to use the sfbrm100PortDefaultVLANId when 802.1Q is enabled on this port. The frames actual VLAN id is replaced with the default VLAN Id. Has no effect when 802.1Q is disabled.

sfbrm100PortDefaultVLANId.name: sfbrm100PortDefaultVLANId
sfbrm100PortDefaultVLANId.description: The default VLAN Id of the port. All untagged frames that are to exit tagged will use the VID of the ingress port on exit. This VID is also used on all frames when 'sfbrm100PortForceDefVLANId' is set.

sfbrm100PortBasedVLANTbl.name: sfbrm100PortBasedVLANTbl
sfbrm100PortBasedVLANTbl.description: Each bit represents ports on the switch. These bits restrict where this port can send frames to, setting the bits to zero will disable this port's ability to egress frames out of the indicated port. Ex: Port 0 is represented by bit 0 in the bitmap. By default all ports can send to all ports.

sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap0.name: sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap0
sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap0.description: All Frames with priority 0 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap1.name: sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap1
sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap1.description: All Frames with priority 1 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap2.name: sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap2
sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap2.description: All Frames with priority 2 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap3.name: sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap3
sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap3.description: All Frames with priority 3 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap4.name: sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap4
sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap4.description: All Frames with priority 4 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap5.name: sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap5
sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap5.description: All Frames with priority 5 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap6.name: sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap6
sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap6.description: All Frames with priority 6 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap7.name: sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap7
sfbrm100PortIEEEPriRemap7.description: All Frames with priority 7 are remapped to this set value inside the switch.

sfbrm100PortVCTest.name: sfbrm100PortVCTest
sfbrm100PortVCTest.description: The virtual cable test can be done using this variable set to perform(1), otherwise the Read-only value notApplicable(2) will be returned.

sfbrm100PortVCTxMDI0Status.name: sfbrm100PortVCTxMDI0Status
sfbrm100PortVCTxMDI0Status.description: The test status of the Tx pair or MDI[0](Gigabit port) depending on port type. normal(1) - Test was successful, cable is normal (no short or open in cable) impedanceMismatch(2)- Test was successful, cable has impedance mismatch. shortInCable(3) - Test was successful, short in cable (impedance < 33 Ohm) openInCable(4) - Test was successful, open in cable (impedance > 333 Ohm) failed(5) - Test failed.

sfbrm100PortTxMDI0Dist.name: sfbrm100PortTxMDI0Dist
sfbrm100PortTxMDI0Dist.description: The cable distance of the Tx pair or MDI[0](Gigabit port) from the tested port. In case of sfbrm100PortVCRxMDIXStatus having a value of 2 - 4, this gives the distance from the port where the impedance occured. In case of normal(1) cable status, one of the listed value is returned.

sfbrm100PortVCRxMDI1Status.name: sfbrm100PortVCRxMDI1Status
sfbrm100PortVCRxMDI1Status.description: The test status of the Rx or MDI[1](Gigabit port) depending on port type. normal(1) - Test was successful, cable is normal (no short or open in cable) impedanceMismatch(2)- Test was successful, cable has impedance mismatch. shortInCable(3) - Test was successful, short in cable (impedance < 33 Ohm) openInCable(4) - Test was successful, open in cable (impedance > 333 Ohm) failed(5) - Test failed.

sfbrm100PortRxMDI1Dist.name: sfbrm100PortRxMDI1Dist
sfbrm100PortRxMDI1Dist.description: The cable distance of the Rx pair or MDI[1](Gigabit port) from the tested port. In case of sfbrm100PortVCRxMDIXStatus having a value of 2 - 4, this gives the distance from the port where the impedance occured.In case of normal(1) cable status, one of the listed value is returned.

sfbrm100PortVCMDI2Status.name: sfbrm100PortVCMDI2Status
